President Donald Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Montana due to flooding that occurred between March 20 and April 10, 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Nathan Knapp has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.